const benefits = [
  {
    icon: '📞',
    title: 'Catches Calls During Active Plumbing',
    text: "Soldering a 22mm copper joint, pressing Viega fittings on a riser, routing PEX through floor joists, gluing a solvent-weld waste system, or commissioning an unvented cylinder — plumbing demands both hands and steady concentration. Missed Call Text Back texts every unanswered caller within seconds."
  },
  {
    icon: '⏱️',
    title: 'Holds Developer Programme Callers',
    text: "A main contractor with the plasterer finishing plot 11 calls his plumber to confirm the second-fix start date. Voicemail? He calls the next plumbing gang. A branded text — 'Thanks for calling — we are fitting sanitaryware and will call back shortly' — holds your programme position."
  },
  {
    icon: '🏷️',
    title: 'Qualified Professional Image',
    text: "An instant branded text from a plumbing contractor signals the organised professionalism that main contractors trust with programme-critical first-fix and second-fix across multi-plot estates."
  },
  {
    icon: '📊',
    title: 'Essential During Full Installation Days',
    text: "Plumbing installation days fill from first-fix at dawn to second-fix sanitaryware at dusk. Every hour under floors, inside stud walls, or in airing cupboards. Missed Call Text Back captures every developer, homeowner, and architect enquiry during your most physically demanding days."
  },
  {
    icon: '📋',
    title: 'Captures Reply Plumbing Details',
    text: "Callers reply with scope — 'bathroom refit, wall-hung WC, walk-in shower, 1930s semi, Headington, want to start June.' Replies arrive on your dashboard before you emerge from the underfloor void."
  },
  {
    icon: '🔄',
    title: 'Pairs with AI Phone Answering',
    text: "Phone Answering conducts full plumbing conversations. Missed Call Text Back covers edge cases — a call during a critical soldered joint, a phone buried under pipe offcuts, or a single-ring hang-up. Together: zero lost plumbing leads."
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "When does the missed call text send?",
    answer: "Your branded text arrives within seconds of the unanswered ring — before the main contractor reaches the next plumbing gang on his contacts list. During full-day first-fix installations where your entire team crawls through floor voids running copper and PEX, this automatic text maintains commercial responsiveness without a single person leaving the joists."
  },
  {
    question: "What does the text message say?",
    answer: "You compose the wording during onboarding and adjust it whenever you choose. A plumbing-specific message reads: 'Thank you for calling [company name]. We are currently installing plumbing and will return your call at the earliest opportunity. Reply with your plumbing requirements for a quicker response.' This conveys active installation capability and invites project specifications."
  },
  {
    question: "Does this replace AI Phone Answering?",
    answer: "The two channels defend your plumbing business as complementary systems. Phone Answering conducts complete conversations — capturing bathroom specifications, developer programmes, unvented cylinder requirements, and emergency leak details. Missed Call Text Back handles rare scenarios — a call while the blow torch heats a capillary joint that cannot be interrupted, a phone signal lost inside a stud wall, or a caller disconnecting before the AI picks up. Both together eliminate plumbing lead loss entirely."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does Missed Call Text Back cost?",
    answer: `This channel is £${pricing.addOn.price}/month as an add-on. A bathroom renovation generates £3,000 to £10,000. Recovering one missed call from a main contractor with a twelve-plot first-fix programme ready to award — through a branded text while you soldered a manifold tee in another airing cupboard — secures revenue that eclipses the channel cost for years.`
  },
  {
    question: "Do callers reply to the text?",
    answer: "Main contractors reply with programme requirements — 'need first-fix gang for 6 houses, copper carcass, Megaflo, UFH, start in 3 weeks, call me.' Homeowners reply with project outlines — 'bathroom refit, want walk-in shower and wall-hung WC, 1950s semi, Summertown.' Letting agents reply with maintenance requests — 'leaking kitchen tap in tenant flat, Cowley Road, need someone this week.' These plumbing leads arrive on your dashboard while the solder sets."
  },
  {
    question: "How is missed call data stored?",
    answer: "Caller details, text replies with property addresses, plumbing specifications, developer schedule information, and contact numbers are encrypted and held on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR. Only you can access the data. Nothing reaches competing plumbing firms or any third party."
  }
];
