<ChannelTradeLayout
  title="Missed Call Text Back for UK Plumbing Contractors | Rapid Receptionist"
  description={`Missed Call Text Back for UK plumbing contractors. Automatically texts callers while you solder joints, press fittings, and commission cylinders. Add-on at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month.`}
  canonicalUrl="/plumbing-contractors/missed-call-text-back/"
  channelName="Missed Call Text Back"
  tradeName="Plumbing Contractor"
  tradeNamePlural="Plumbing Contractors"
  tradeSlug="plumbing-contractors"
  headline="Missed Call Text Back for UK Plumbing Contractor Companies"
  accentWord="Plumbing"
  subhead="It is 10am on a Thursday. You are in the airing cupboard of a new-build house in Didcot — commissioning a Gledhill Stainlesslite Plus 210 unvented cylinder. The pre-charge on the expansion vessel reads 3 bar, the mains incoming pressure is 3.5 bar with the PRV set correctly, the T&P relief valve is connected through the tundish, and the D1 and D2 discharge pipes terminate visibly outside. You are filling the system, venting the air locks, and checking every joint for leaks before signing the G3 commissioning certificate. Four calls come in between 9am and noon. Your phone is in your jacket downstairs, the airing cupboard barely large enough for you and the cylinder. Without Missed Call Text Back, two voicemails — 'bathroom quote' and 'developer calling about first fix' — two hang-ups. With it, all four receive texts within seconds. The first replies at 10:20am: 'Hi — main contractor here, building 16 three-bed semis in Wantage. Need first-fix plumbing: 22mm and 15mm copper, SVP to two bathrooms per house, mains entry with PRV, PEX manifold UFH ground floor. Second fix: Megaflo Eco 210i, Ideal Standard sanitaryware, TMV2 on baths. Blockwork ready in five weeks. Can you price per plot and confirm you can do four per week? Call me when free.' At the lunch break you review. Friday you call: Wantage 16 semis, copper carcass, SVP×2, PRV, PEX UFH, Megaflo Eco 210i, Ideal Standard, TMV2, 4 plots/week, 5-week start."
  scenario="It is 3pm on a wet February Monday. You have been under the ground floor of a Victorian terrace in Walton Street since 8am — replacing corroded lead water mains with 15mm barrier PEX, working in a 400mm crawl space with standing water from the rain seeping through the airbricks. Six missed calls between 8am and 3pm. Without Missed Call Text Back, you emerge at 3pm: six unknowns, one voicemail — 'need a plumber for a leak,' five gone forever. With Missed Call Text Back, all six received texts. Reply one: 'homeowner Botley — new en-suite in loft conversion, need hot/cold feeds, soil stack connection for WC, shower waste, and UFH, architect drawings ready.' Reply two: 'builder Abingdon — extension needs all plumbing connections, kitchen and utility, before the plasterer next Thursday.' Reply three: 'letting agent — burst pipe behind bath panel in tenant flat, Cowley, water isolated, ceiling below damp, need repair today.' Reply four: 'homeowner Summertown — want to replace gravity cylinder with Megaflo for better shower pressure, need survey and quote.' Reply five: 'architect — luxury basement bathroom, freestanding bath, walk-in shower, macerator drainage, North Oxford, send drawings.' Reply six: 'homeowner Witney — dripping kitchen tap, think it needs new cartridges, Bristan.' Six leads. Monday evening you prioritise — the burst pipe for immediate response, the Thursday builder connection, then the rest."
  benefits={benefits}
  faqs={faqs}
  channelPageUrl="/construction-trades/missed-call-text-back/"
  tradePageUrl="/plumbing-contractors/ai-receptionist/"
  ctaHeadline="Recover Six Plumbing Leads from One Wet February Monday"
  ctaSubhead={`While you replaced lead mains in a 400mm crawl space, six callers missed you. Six texts went out. A loft en-suite, a builder connection, a burst pipe, a Megaflo upgrade, a basement bathroom, and a dripping tap. Add-on at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month.`}
